Ask HN: Is there any service/application for logging locations I’ve visited
text:
I want to keep a log of locations I’ve visited.

When I was on Android I was using SmarterTime [1]. It had a nice visualisation of the locations I’ve travelled throughout last day/week/month, etc.

But now that I’ve switched to iOS, I cannot find any similar application.

I want to know if there’s any similar service (preferably self hosted due to the sensitivity of the data). With a client app that could be installed on mobile devices.

[1] https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.smartertime&hl=en_IN&gl=US

What can I buy instead of an RPi for my nephew to learn to program on?
text:
I just need a simple and cheap computer for my nephew (11yrs old) to learn to program on. It needs to run Scratch and python and that's it. Raspberry pi's are sold out everywhere in the UK. 
I need it now because he just has been given a programming book for Xmas (by me) and he's excited to start!
